@@ -10,34 +10,242 @@ FMLV: Past runs - Trends and insights
 Feature development — core service implementation for past runs, trends, and insights.
 
 ## System Context
-> How does this repo's contribution fit into the overall feature? Reference the
-> [Overall Design Spec](https://dev.azure.com/msdata/A365/_git/FeatureRegistry?path=/Features/active/5054458/overalldesign-spec.md)
-> in the Feature Registry for the system-level view.
+
+This repo (workload-fabriclivetable) is the core service implementation for the Insights & Trends feature. It provides:
+
+- Delta table writers that persist DAG execution metrics to the `_mlv_system` schema
+- REST API endpoints that read metrics via SQL Analytics Endpoint
+- Feature flag gating for safe rollout
+
+The overall feature spans 4 repos (see the [Overall Design Spec](https://dev.azure.com/msdata/A365/_git/FeatureRegistry?path=/Features/active/5054458/overalldesign-spec.md) in the Feature Registry), but this repo contains ~90% of the feature implementation.
 
 ## Design Goals
-> What qualities is this area-specific design optimizing for?
+
+- **Never block the DAG:** All metrics writes are fire-and-forget hooks
+- **Zero user setup:** Tables auto-created, data auto-populated on every DAG completion
+- **CU-conscious:** Reuse warm Spark session, cache API responses (60s TTL)
+- **Testable:** Every external interaction behind an interface (`ISparkWriter`, `IQueryService`)
+- **Incremental delivery:** Feature flag gated, per-table parallel writers for isolation
 
 ## Detailed Design
-> Repo-specific implementation design. Include:
-> - Components to add or modify
-> - Internal APIs and data structures
-> - State management and lifecycle
-> - Error handling and retry logic
+
+### Hook Architecture
+
+- **`InsightsTableCreationHook`** — Creates `_mlv_system` schema + 3 tables (idempotent, runs once)
+- **`InsightsMetricsDataWriteHook`** — Orchestrates 3 parallel table writers:
+  - **`RunMetricsTableWriter`** — Collects DAG-level metrics, generates PySpark `MERGE INTO sys_run_metrics`
+  - **`NodeMetricsTableWriter`** — Collects per-MLV node metrics, generates PySpark `MERGE INTO sys_node_metrics`
+  - **`ErrorMetricsTableWriter`** — Collects error details, generates PySpark `MERGE INTO sys_error_metrics`
+- **`DagHookUtils`** — Shared utilities for PySpark code generation (escape, format, null-guard)
+
+### API Architecture
+
+- **`LiveTableInsightsController`** — 3 endpoints registered in `LiveTableController` routing, gated by `[FeatureGate(FeatureNames.FLTInsightsMetrics)]` (returns 404 when disabled)
+- **`InsightsQueryBuilder`** — Builds parameterized T-SQL for each endpoint (static class, all queries use `SqlParameter`)
+- **`SqlEndpointQueryService`** — Executes queries via `SqlConnection` to Lakehouse SQL Analytics Endpoint (OBO token)
+- **`IInsightsQueryService`** — Interface for query execution (enables unit testing via mocks)
+
+### Key Classes
+
+| Class | Namespace | Purpose |
+|-------|-----------|---------|
+| `InsightsTableCreationHook` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | Schema + table DDL |
+| `InsightsMetricsDataWriteHook` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | Hook orchestrator |
+| `RunMetricsTableWriter` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | `sys_run_metrics` writer |
+| `NodeMetricsTableWriter` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | `sys_node_metrics` writer |
+| `ErrorMetricsTableWriter` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | `sys_error_metrics` writer |
+| `InsightsMetricsTableManager` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | Table creation manager |
+| `DagHookUtils` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Insights` | PySpark codegen utilities |
+| `LiveTableInsightsController` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Controllers` | REST API controller |
+| `InsightsQueryBuilder` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Trends` | T-SQL query builder (static) |
+| `SqlEndpointQueryService` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Trends` | SQL endpoint query execution |
+| `InsightsSummaryResponse` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Trends.Models` | Summary DTO |
+| `InsightsRunResponse` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Trends.Models` | Single run DTO |
+| `InsightsRunsPageResponse` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Trends.Models` | Paginated runs wrapper (Items + TotalCount) |
+| `InsightsTrendsResponse` | `Microsoft.LiveTable.Service.Trends.Models` | Trends + top errors DTO |
 
 ## Data Model
-> New or modified data models specific to this repo.
+
+3 Delta tables in `_mlv_system` schema:
+
+- **`sys_run_metrics`** — One row per DAG run (`iterationId`, `status`, `durationMs`, `refreshMode`, error fields, `mlvCount`, `successCount`, `failedCount`, `skippedCount`). Partitioned by `RunDate`.
+- **`sys_node_metrics`** — One row per MLV per run (`iterationId`, `nodeId`, `mlvName`, `mlvId`, `mlvNamespace`, `status`, `durationMs`, error fields, `addedRowsCount`, `droppedRowsCount`, `detailsPageLink`, `refreshPolicy`). Partitioned by `iterationId`.
+- **`sys_error_metrics`** — Error details per node (`iterationId`, `nodeId`, `errorCode`, `errorMessage`, `errorSource`).
 
 ## API Design
-> New or modified APIs exposed or consumed by this repo.
+
+3 Phase 1 endpoints under `/v1/workspaces/{workspaceId}/lakehouses/{lakehouseId}/liveTable/insights/`:
+
+### GET `/insights/summary`
+
+Returns aggregate metrics for the selected date range.
+
+| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
+|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
+| `dateRange` | int | No | 7 | Days to look back (1-90) |
+| `startTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit start time (overrides dateRange) |
+| `endTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit end time (overrides dateRange) |
+
+**Response:** `InsightsSummaryResponse`
+```json
+{
+  "totalRuns": 42,
+  "totalRunsDeltaPct": -4.1,
+  "successRatePct": 85.7,
+  "successRateDeltaPct": 1.5,
+  "avgDurationMin": 8.4,
+  "avgDurationDeltaPct": 3.7,
+  "failedRuns": 3,
+  "failedRunsDeltaPct": -14.3,
+  "skippedRuns": 2,
+  "cancelledRuns": 1,
+  "completedRuns": 36,
+  "lastUpdatedAt": "2026-04-26T20:30:00Z"
+}
+```
+
+The `*DeltaPct` fields are **period-over-period** comparisons: current period vs previous period of the same length. For `dateRange=7`, compares last 7 days vs the 7 days before that. For explicit `startTime/endTime`, the previous period is `duration` days before `startTime`. Fields are `null` when no previous period data exists. `successRateDeltaPct` is a percentage-point difference; all others are percentage change `((current - previous) / previous * 100)`.
+
+### GET `/insights/runs`
+
+Returns paginated list of individual DAG runs with filtering.
+
+| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
+|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
+| `dateRange` | int | No | 7 | Days to look back (1-90) |
+| `startTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit start time |
+| `endTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit end time |
+| `statuses` | string | No | — | Comma-separated: Completed, Failed, Skipped, Cancelled |
+| `refreshModes` | string | No | — | Comma-separated: Optimal, Full, Incremental, NoRefresh |
+| `displayName` | string | No | — | Partial match filter (SQL LIKE %term%) |
+| `page` | int | No | 1 | Page number (1-based) |
+| `pageSize` | int | No | 50 | Items per page (1-200) |
+
+**Response:** `InsightsRunsPageResponse`
+```json
+{
+  "items": [
+    {
+      "iterationId": "abc-123",
+      "displayName": "Run #42",
+      "status": "Completed",
+      "startedAt": "2026-04-26T20:00:00Z",
+      "endedAt": "2026-04-26T20:08:24Z",
+      "durationMs": 504000,
+      "refreshMode": "Optimal",
+      "errorCode": null,
+      "errorMessage": null,
+      "errorSource": null,
+      "totalNodes": 5,
+      "succeededNodes": 5,
+      "failedNodes": 0,
+      "skippedNodes": 0
+    }
+  ],
+  "totalCount": 42
+}
+```
+
+### GET `/insights/trends`
+
+Returns daily/weekly trend data for run status distribution.
+
+| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
+|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
+| `dateRange` | int | No | 7 | Days to look back (1-90) |
+| `startTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit start time |
+| `endTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit end time |
+| `groupBy` | string | No | day | Aggregation period: `day` or `week` |
+
+**Response:** `InsightsTrendsResponse`
+```json
+{
+  "dailyTrend": [
+    { "runDate": "2026-04-26", "completed": 5, "failed": 1, "skipped": 0, "cancelled": 0 }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+When `groupBy=week`, `runDate` contains the Monday of each ISO week (e.g., `"2026-04-21"`), aggregated via `DATEADD(DAY, -(DATEPART(WEEKDAY, run_date) - 2), run_date)` cast to `VARCHAR(10)`.
+
+### GET `/insights/errors/top`
+
+Returns top error codes across all failed **nodes** (not DAG runs), enabling visibility into multi-node failures within a single DAG. Queries `sys_node_metrics` to surface per-node error codes with error source classification.
+
+| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |
+|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|
+| `dateRange` | int | No | 7 | Days to look back (1-90) |
+| `startTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit start time |
+| `endTime` | ISO 8601 | No | — | Explicit end time |
+| `limit` | int | No | 5 | Top N error codes to return (1-20) |
+
+**Response:** `InsightsTopErrorsResponse`
+```json
+{
+  "topErrors": [
+    { "errorCode": "MLV_LINEAGE_CREATION_FAILURE", "errorSource": "System", "count": 3 },
+    { "errorCode": "MLV_NOT_FOUND", "errorSource": "User", "count": 1 }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+### Feature Gate
+
+All endpoints are gated by `[FeatureGate(FeatureNames.FLTInsightsMetrics)]` at the controller class level. When the feature flag is disabled, all endpoints return **404 Not Found** (not 501).
+
+### Validation
+
+- `refreshModes` values are validated against a whitelist: `Optimal`, `Full`, `Incremental`, `NoRefresh`. Invalid values return 400.
+- `statuses` values are validated against: `Completed`, `Failed`, `Skipped`, `Cancelled`. Invalid values return 400.
+- `groupBy` must be `day` or `week`. Invalid values return 400.
+- `limit` is clamped to 1-20 range.
+- `dateRange` is clamped to 1-90 range.
+
+### Deferred Items
+
+- **Response caching** (60s TTL, R-0211) — deferred to Phase 1.1
+- **sortBy/sortOrder** on `/runs` — needs PM to specify sortable columns
+- **`/runs/{iterationId}`** detail endpoint — Phase 2
+- **`/errors/top`** as standalone endpoint — currently bundled in `/trends` response
+- **Insight cards** (`/cards`, `/cards/{id}/dismiss`) — Phase 2 (Insight Engine)
 
 ## Security Considerations
-> Repo-specific security concerns: input validation, auth, data protection.
+
+- Parameterized T-SQL everywhere (`SqlParameter`) — no string interpolation
+- MWC token auth via existing FLT auth middleware
+- Workspace RBAC enforced — no cross-workspace data access
+- No PII in Delta tables (no user emails, AAD tokens, etc.)
 
 ## Testing Strategy
-> Unit tests, integration tests, coverage targets (90% minimum).
+
+- **251 unit tests** across 3 test classes:
+  - `InsightsQueryBuilderTests` — 35 tests covering SQL generation (parameterized queries, LIKE patterns, CAST for week grouping, refresh mode whitelist, limit clamping)
+  - `LiveTableInsightsControllerTests` — 49 tests covering controller behavior (parameter validation, feature gate, pagination, error handling)
+  - `SqlEndpointQueryServiceTests` — Mock-based tests for query service interface
+- API controller tests mock `IInsightsQueryService` interface
+- Unit tests per writer class (mock `ISparkWriter`)
+- CST integration tests via SparkCST Official pipeline
+- Dev mode E2E validation against EDog with real data
+- Coverage gate enforced in CI pipeline
 
 ## Dependencies
-> Internal and external dependencies specific to this repo's implementation.
 
-## Open Questions
-> Unresolved design questions for this repo's contribution.
+- `ISparkWriter` — for Delta table writes via GTS
+- `IInsightsQueryService` — interface for SQL endpoint reads (OBO token)
+- `SqlEndpointQueryService` — concrete implementation using `SqlConnection`
+- `InsightsMetricsTableManager` — for table creation
+- `FeatureNames.FLTInsightsMetrics` — feature flag
+- `FeatureGateAttribute` — reads from `CustomerCapacityAsyncLocalContext` + `IFeatureFlighter`
+
+## Open Questions / PM Decisions Pending
+
+See [PM Discrepancy Report](../../docs/pm-discrepancy-report.md) for full details. Key items:
+
+1. **S2 — Period-over-period trend arrows** — Backend computes or UX layer handles? (P0)
+2. **S4 — 60-second response caching** (R-0211) — Deferred to Phase 1.1
+3. **R5 — sortBy/sortOrder params** — PM to specify which columns are sortable
+4. **R6 — Status: Completed vs Succeeded** — Canonical value needs PM decision
+5. **T3 — `/errors/top` bundled in `/trends`** vs separate endpoint
+6. **T4 — Status filter on `/trends`** — IC-05 says filters apply to charts
+7. **X1 — PII: `submit_user` in Delta table** — R-0503 compliance (P0)
+8. **X2 — Retention 90d vs 180d** — Spec conflict needs resolution
